      "writtenOn": "2017-07-18T17:07:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is a bit messy, because it was tailored to the digests. \nI would suggest to do the following: \n\n- extract the imageID or the diffID from the URL\n- call additional functions on the IDPathMapper, i.e. \n    d.mapper.IsValidImageID(imgageID)\n    and \n    d.mapper.IsValidDiffID(diffID)\n- follow the same logic as previously. \n\nThe underlying issue is how the imageID and the diffID are contained in URL. \nIn Gold it can happen, that an image is requested, but has not been downloaded from \nGS. That\u0027s why it validates the digest (within reason) and downloads the image if necessary. \n\nAlternatively we could get rid of these checks and just return the image if it exists on disk.",
